Welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Leigh Ann
Caldwell, coming to you on this early springlike weekend despite that terri=
ble time change.

=C2=A0

For today=E2=80=99s issue, I=E2=80=99ve eavesdropped on the inner dialogue =
of Democrats as they face this week=E2=80=99s vote on Mike Johnson=E2=80=99=
s Trump-endorsed bill to fund the government beyond Friday. This is the fir=
st real test to see whether Democrats can meaningfully disrupt the Republic=
an
agenda. But, in true Democratic fashion, the party is wrestling with itself=
 over how to proceed on the vote=E2=80=94and perhaps most pointedly, whethe=
r approving the bill would be seen by voters as endorsing Elon Musk=E2=80=
=99s slash-and-burn DOGE offensive.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* Trust deficit: It=E2=80=99s not just Democrats who are twisting in the wi=
nd ahead of the funding vote. House conservatives who rarely vote to fund t=
he government, and often enjoy government shutdowns, are also under immense=
 pressure to vote =E2=80=9Caye.=E2=80=9D Johnson is leaning on Trump to bri=
ng wayward colleagues on board.

If Trump weren=E2=80=99t in the White House, there=E2=80=99s no way Johnson=
 would be able to unite his entire party behind him=E2=80=94too many Republ=
icans, especially fiscally
conservative hardliners, just don=E2=80=99t trust him. They=E2=80=99re frus=
trated by his survivalist willingness to turn to Democrats to pass legislat=
ion, as he did for the past few funding bills and last year=E2=80=99s defen=
se spending deal. (No recent Republican speaker has funded the government w=
ithout the help of Democrats.) In particular, Johnson=E2=80=99s decision to=
 wrap aid to Ukraine inside a border security bill was seen as forcing thei=
r hand.

Trump has instructed Republicans to approve this week=E2=80=99s bill, both
on social media and during a recent White House meeting with a group of abo=
ut 20 virulently anti-government Republicans. While he persuaded many to ba=
ck the deal, including Freedom Caucus chair Andy Harris=E2=80=94who is, ast=
onishingly, advocating on social media against a shutdown=E2=80=94I=E2=80=
=99m told that not all of them are on board just yet. Many of them have bui=
lt their careers on opposing government funding. Trump=E2=80=99s cover is t=
he only reason they=E2=80=99re even considering it.
* The economy, stupid: Trump=E2=80=99s whipsaw actions on tariffs and weake=
ning economic indicators are prompting a lot of latent recession fears. On =
Fox News=E2=80=99s Sunday Morning Futures, Maria Bartiromo brought up the R=
-word directly to Trump. =E2=80=9CI hate to predict things like that,=E2=80=
=9D he told her. He went on to say, as he=E2=80=99s said before, that there=
 will be =E2=80=9Ca transition=E2=80=9D before things are =E2=80=9Cgreat.=
=E2=80=9D That aligns with what Treasury Secretary Scott
Bessent signaled on CNBC last week, when he acknowledged that =E2=80=9Cther=
e=E2=80=99s going to be a detox period=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94another apparent eu=
phemism for an economic downturn. Meanwhile, Commerce Secretary Howard Lutn=
ick seemingly walked it all back in a very audience-of-one interview on Mee=
t the Press, during which he noted that the administration=E2=80=99s policy=
 will =E2=80=9Cabsolutely not=E2=80=9D lead to a slowdown. =E2=80=9CThere=
=E2=80=99s going to be no recession in America,=E2=80=9D Lutnick added.

This commentary is
unlikely to reassure institutional investors=E2=80=94who have been rotating=
 out of U.S. equities into short-dated Treasuries, Chinese tech stocks, and=
 European weapons manufacturers=E2=80=94or even Republican members of Congr=
ess. (Read Dry Powder, my partner Bill Cohan=E2=80=99s excellent Puck priva=
te email, to learn what Wall Street C.E.O.s are privately
saying ( https://puck.news/richard-haass-and-the-wise-men-of-wall-street-so=
und-off-on-trump/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%=
283%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283=
%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3D=
f6c60617da42abd12a ) under their breath.) House members, of course, will be=
 forced to craft more nuanced talking points in their districts as they fac=
e elections in a year and a half.

Now for the main event=E2=80=A6

